-- China Arrests Seven For Smuggling 4,196 Tons of Rare Earth, Xinhua Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-14T13:45:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/china-arrests-seven-for-smuggling-4-196-tons-of-rare-earth-xinhua-reports.html

          
          
             China arrested seven people on
suspicion of smuggling 4,196 tons of rare earth metals and their
compounds, the official Xinhua News Agency said today citing the
customs agency.  
 The Nanning branch of the General Administration of Customs
in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region uncovered the smuggling ring
that involved rare earth elements valued at 109 million yuan,
Xinhua said citing the agency.  
 Rare earths are considered strategically important 
resources and exports are strictly controlled, Xinhua said.  
          
          


  


        